The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and algorithm design (cs.DS), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economic theory (cs.EC). The use of LP-relative approximation algorithms suggests a connection to theoretical computer science and machine learning (cs.LG).
